  "local_port": 46208,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I configure a universal remote?",
  "response": "Configuring a universal remote can vary slightly depending on the brand and model of the remote. However, the general process is similar across most devices. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you set up your universal remote:\n\n### Step 1: Prepare Your Devices\n1. **Identify Devices**: Make a list of the devices you want to control (e.g., TV, DVD player, sound system).\n2. **Turn On Devices**: Make sure all the devices are powered on before you begin the setup process.\n\n### Step 2: Insert Batteries\n1. Open the battery compartment on the back of the remote.\n2. Insert fresh batteries, making sure to match the +/- signs correctly.\n3. Close the compartment.\n\n### Step 3: Find the Code\n1. **Check the Manual**: Look for the user manual that came with your universal remote, as it will contain a list of device codes.\n2. **Online Code Search**: If you don\u2019t have the manual, visit the manufacturer\u2019s website to find the correct codes for your devices.\n\n### Step 4: Program Your Remote\n1. **Turn On the Device**: Power on the device you want to program (TV, DVD player, etc.).\n2. **Enter Programming Mode**:\n   - Usually, this is done by pressing and holding the \"Setup\" button until a red light turns on and then releasing it.\n   - The light should stay on.\n3. **Enter the Device Code**:\n   - Using the number pad on the remote, input the code from the list.\n   - After entering the code, the red light should turn off. If it stays on, the code was incorrect; try the next code.\n4. **Test the Remote**: Try using your remote to control the device (like changing the channel or adjusting the volume) to ensure it\u2019s working.\n\n### Step 5: Repeat for Additional Devices\n1. **Repeat Steps**: If you have other devices to add, repeat steps 1-4 for each device.\n2. Use the appropriate mode button (e.g., TV, DVD) before programming each device.\n\n### Step 6: Troubleshoot if Necessary\n- **Try Different Codes**: Sometimes it takes a few tries with different codes before one works.\n- **Reset the Remote**: If you encounter issues, you may try resetting the remote (check the manual for instructions on how to do this).\n\n### Step 7: Additional Features\n- **Setup Preferred Settings**: Once the device responds, you can configure other settings like input sources or macros (if supported).\n- **Use Auto-Search**: Some universal remotes have an auto-search feature that can scan for the right code automatically.\n\n### Step 8: Save Configuration\n- Ensure the configuration is saved (if necessary) by following any prompts given by the remote.\n\n### Conclusion\nOnce you\u2019ve programmed all your devices, you should be able to control them with the universal remote. If you have any issues, refer back to the user manual or the manufacturer's website for help.",
